values.value: For bolts of the class 8.8 (Component length > 50mm) and 10.9 (generally) from Maraform-wire the finished units must be warm up with a temperature of 250 - 300°C /1 hour on air to reach the lasting elongation < 12,5µm in the test load attempt and the yield strenght (10.9) acc. DIN EN ISO 898.
